BDD
-> login.feature 
* file contains test scenarios
* using normal english language
* uses for business purpose and non-technical persons to understand what are the scenarios are going to automate.
* Listing the behaiviour of the application
-> login.steps.js 
* file contains automation code of the scenarios written in the login.feature file.
* It is a step definition file

Hooks in cucumber
-> BeforeAll- runs only once before all other scenarios
eg: browser launch
-> AfterAll- runs only one time after all other scenarios are completed.
eg: browser close or logout
-> Before- executes before each scenario execution
eg: page setup and all
-> After- executes after each scenario execution
eg: 
-> BeforeStep- executes before every step in a scenario
eg: Screenshot taking
-> AfterStep- executes after every step in a scenario
eg: 

-> Command to run individual file in the step definition
npx cucumber-js features/inventory.feature --require step-definitions/*.js
-> Command to run all files in the step definition
 npx cucumber-js --require step-definitions/**/*.js    

